Requires a valid Authorization header, 400s if user owns project or if project doesn't exist.

Uses an upsert query to initialize a project's view count to 1, increments it thereafter.

pulltitle: force type identity on isOwner arguments
pullsbody:
fixes https://github.com/mozilla/api.webmaker.org/issues/130

Right now we have a situation where we might compare `1` to `'1'`, which will fail due to type inequality, even if they represent the same id. This patch fixes that by forcing all incoming data to string before evaluating.

pulltitle: force type identity on isOwner arguments
pullsbody:
fixes https://github.com/mozilla/api.webmaker.org/issues/130

Right now we have a situation where we might compare `1` to `'1'`, which will fail due to type inequality, even if they represent the same id. This patch fixes that by forcing all incoming data to string before evaluating.
This is the same as #108, (reverted in #128) but includes a commit that fixes a failure caused by the remix data method caching a mocked data response.

pulltitle: Cache server method reponses, test configuration and caching
pullsbody:
Fixes #37

This patch refactors the webmaker-postgre-adapter plugin and includes caching for all 'find' queries.

responses are cached for 60 seconds, and go stale in 30 seconds. if a stale cache is hit, it tries to refresh it, but if it takes longer than 100 ms it returns the cached version and updates the cached value in the background. 

we can totally tweak the cache numbers
pull_commit_message: Cache server method reponses, test configuration and caching
